  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Ioxus Project</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">1. Amid growing calls to reduce carbon emissions worldwide, developing countries like China have become strong advocates of developing a low carbon economy. This project would contribute to development of the clean technology sector in China and assist the government of China to reduce GHG emissions from buses through cost effective and environmentally responsible solutions. 2. GHG impact is larger by saving 5-12 percent in 90 percent of cars through mild hybrids than by saving 50 percent in 0.1 percent of cars through EVs. 3. This project would enable product transfer to other developing regions, such as Southeast Asia.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Founded in 2007, Ioxus develops and manufactures ultracapacitors with higher power and energy density than traditional ultracapacitors at lower cost. Its technology and products can be applied across different sectors, including start-stop applications for transportation, pitch control for wind turbines, industrial automation and power tools.  The funds raised will be deployed to expand facilities, develop sales and marketing, and expand product offerings and application portfolio.</narrative>
  </description>
